            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Hd1e108">Rubrica 5</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De militia et officio et laudibus militum et sacramento eorum</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>
      ¶ De militia et officio et laudibus militum
      <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>et sacramento eorum. Rubrica. 5.
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e121">
               <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>Egetius de re mili. l. 2.
      <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>t. 5. <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e127">Iurant mili
        <lb ed="#V" n="20" break="no"/>tes omnia se strenue facturos que
        <lb ed="#V" n="21"/>preceperit impator: nunquam desertu
        <lb ed="#V" n="22"/>ros militiam: nec mortem recusaturos pro re
        <lb ed="#V" n="23"/>publica. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e139"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e141"> 18. t. In congruum videretur impera
        <lb ed="#V" n="24" break="no"/>toris militem qui veste et annona publica
        <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>pasceretur vtilitatibus vacare puatis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e150"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e152"> 23
        <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>t. et p. Miles sacramento lectus ab exerci
        <lb ed="#V" n="27" break="no"/>tio armorum vel nouellus vel vetustus ces
        <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>sare non debet: cui pugnandum est pro salu
        <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>te propria vel libertate communi. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e164"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e166"> 31. e. Pu
        <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>blicis debent vtilitatibus insudare qui no
        <lb ed="#V" n="31" break="no"/>men dedere militie. quid enim agat homo
        <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>si professo desit officio </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e176"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e178"> Li. 3 t. 3. Diuitia
        <lb ed="#V" n="33" break="no"/>rum secura non est possessio nisi armorum
        <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>defensione seruetur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e186"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e188"> 10. t. Quis dubitat ar
        <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>tem bellicam rebus omnibus esse potiorem:
        <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>per quam libertas retinetur: et dignitas prouin
        <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>cie propagatur conseruatur imperium. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e198">
               <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e202">¶ Cassiodorus: epistolarum. el. i. e. 16. Ani
        <lb ed="#V" n="39" break="no"/>mus ipse in audaciam non potest esse pro
        <lb ed="#V" n="40" break="no"/>nus qui diuersa cura fuerit sollicitus. hanc
        <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>merito expeditionem nominauere maiores:
        <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>quia mens deuota preliis non debet aliis co
        <lb ed="#V" n="43" break="no"/>gitationibus occupari. Constat tempore ne
        <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>cessitatis illum probari fortissimum virum
        <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>qui se per multa non distrahit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e221"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e223"> Lib. 11. e. <!--290.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>37. Sub incerta vita militia est. </quote>
            </p>
